File->New

(Same as File->Open)

This is used to start a new Movieola project, or continue on an
existing project. It brings up a file selector, using which you can
either select an existing project folder, or type in a new name. If
you are running Movieola for the first time, it creates a
"Movieola_projects" folder in your home. It is recommended (but not
mandatory) that you create all your Movieola projects inside this
folder.

Movieola tries to shield the user from the mysteries of UNIX by
providing a separate folder for each project, into which all the work
is saved. The project folder has a "scene" folder, which contains the
main scene file, all object files that you create and texture .rgb
files used by the objects. Then it has an "image" folder, which
contains rendered and finished images. It also has a "NOTES" file to
maintain a log on your project (see File->Notes).
    
NOTE: If you use file operations outside Movieola (Example: Workspace
or UNIX shell), DO NOT remove or rename any folders under the project
folder, even if they are empty. Also do not touch the main scene file.

